==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|diurnalis|diurnālis|lang=la}}, from {{term|dies|diēs|day|lang=la}}. Cognate with {{term|journal|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|[daɪˈɜː(ɹ).nəɫ]}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/daɪˈɝ.nəl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-diurnal.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|ɜː(r)nəl}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Happening or [[occur]]ring during [[daylight]], or primarily [[active]] during that time.
#: ''Most birds are '''diurnal'''.''
# {{context|botany}} Said of a flower [[open]], or releasing its [[perfume]] during daylight hours, but not at night.
# Having a daily [[cycle]] that is completed every 24 hours, usually referring to [[tasks]], [[processes]], [[tides]], or [[sunrise]] to [[sunset]].
# {{context|uncommon}} Done [[once]] every day; [[daily]], [[quotidian]].
# {{context|archaic}} [[publish|Published]] daily.

